        Suggested change











            As an example, suppose we have an interceptor that stores method's return values into a cache.



            The corresponding interceptor binding would be called `@Cached` and would be declared as `@Repeatable`.



            If we wanted to store the return value into two caches at the same time, we would add `@Cached` twice:







            [source,java]



            ----



            @ApplicationScoped



            class AllEncompassingService {



              @Cached(cacheName = "foo")



              @Cached(cacheName = "bar")



              BigData heavyComputation() {



                // ...



              }



            As an example, suppose we have an interceptor that removes all entries from a cache.



            The corresponding interceptor binding would be called `@CacheInvalidateAll` and would be declared as `@Repeatable`.



            If we wanted to clear two caches at the same time, we would add `@CacheInvalidateAll` twice:







            [source,java]



            ----



            @ApplicationScoped



            class AllEncompassingService {



              @CacheInvalidateAll(cacheName = "foo")



              @CacheInvalidateAll(cacheName = "bar")



              void clearBothCaches() {



                // ...



              }






When this PR is merged, @CacheInvalidateAll will even become an interceptor binding (it's a simple annotation right now).
